    "description": {
      "value": "<p>This advanced form of Risai Butsu exerts such power that the target's chest cavity looks like it might cave in. This technique functions as Juuryu: Risai Butsu, except as noted above, and the attack instead deals unarmed damage as though you were two size categories larger, plus 2 per Strength Rank you currently benefit from. If hit, the target also suffers 1d6 damage per two levels (10d6 maximum; Fortitude halves).</p>\n\n\n<p><b>Mastery:</b> The third step has the target fall @Condition[prone]{prone} if they fail their Fortitude save.<br><br>The fifth step increases the bonus damage by 2d6, and increases the maximum bonus damage to 12d6.</p>\n",
